Class Storage

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Storage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class Storage
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is responsible for storing and retrieving all the Student objects and Course objects in the program.

      • registerForCourse

        public void registerForCourse​(java.lang.String userId,
                              java.lang.String courseCodeToBeAdded,
                              IndexNumber indexNumberToBeAdded)
                       throws CourseRegisteredException,
                              ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                              NoVacancyException,
                              CourseInWaitListException,
                              ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException,
                              MaxAuExceededException
        Register a student for a course and index number.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user id of the student to register the course and index number for.
        courseCodeToBeAdded - The course code of the course to register the student for.
        indexNumberToBeAdded - The IndexNumber object to register the student for.
        Throws:
        CourseRegisteredException - if the student is already taking the course that is to be registered for.
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the student has another index number that clashes with the index number to be registered for.
        NoVacancyException - if the index number to be registered for has no vacancy.
        CourseInWaitListException - if the course to be registered for is already in the student's wait list.
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the index number to be registered for clashes with another index number that is already in the student's wait list.
        MaxAuExceededException - if the AU of the course to be registered plus the current AU taken by the student (both registered and in wait list) exceeds the maximum number of AU allowed to be taken by the student.

      • swapIndexNumber

        public void swapIndexNumber​(java.lang.String userId,
                            java.lang.String courseCodeToBeSwapped,
                            IndexNumber newIndexNumber)
                     throws ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                            NoVacancySwapException,
                            SameIndexNumberSwapException,
                            ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException
        Swap index number for a course that a student is registered for.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user id of the student for which the index number will be swapped.
        courseCodeToBeSwapped - The course code of the course for which the index number will swapped for the student.
        newIndexNumber - The IndexNumber object that represents the new index number that the student wants to swap to.
        Throws:
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the new index number to be swapped clashes with a registered index number of the student.
        NoVacancySwapException - if the new index number to be swapped has no vacancies.
        SameIndexNumberSwapException - if the new index number is the same as current index number of the student.
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the new index number to be swapped clashes with an index number that is in the wait list of the student.

      • swapIndexWithPeer

        public void swapIndexWithPeer​(java.lang.String userId,
                              java.lang.String peerUserId,
                              java.lang.String courseCodeToBeSwapped)
                       throws PeerClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException,
                              SameIndexNumberSwapException,
                              ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException,
                              ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                              PeerClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException
        Swap an index number with another peer.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user id of the student initiating the swap.
        peerUserId - The user id of the peer that is swapping with the student.
        courseCodeToBeSwapped - The course code of the course that is to be swapped by the student and the peer.
        Throws:
        SameIndexNumberSwapException - if the student and the peer has the same index number.
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the peer's index number clashes with an index number that is in the student's wait list.
        PeerClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the student's index number clashes with an index number that is in the peer's registered list.
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the peer's index number clashes with an index number that is in the student's registered list.
        PeerClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the student's index number clashes with an index number that is in the peer's wait list.

        public void dropCourseFromWaitList​(java.lang.String userId,
                                   java.lang.String courseCodeToBeDropped,
                                   IndexNumber indexNumberToBeDropped)
        Drop a course from the wait list for a particular student.

      • dropCourseAndRegisterNextStudentInWaitList

        public void dropCourseAndRegisterNextStudentInWaitList​(java.lang.String userId,
                                                       java.lang.String courseCodeToBeDropped,
                                                       IndexNumber indexNumberToBeDropped)
                                                throws CourseInWaitListException,
                                                       ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                                                       CourseRegisteredException,
                                                       NoVacancyException,
                                                       ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException,
                                                       MaxAuExceededException
        Contains the logic to drop a course and the index number and register the next student in the wait list for that index number. The exceptions can be ignored since the exceptions should have been taken care of when the index number is * added into the student's wait list.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user id of the student for which the course and index number will be dropped.
        courseCodeToBeDropped - The course code of the course which the student wants to drop.
        indexNumberToBeDropped - The IndexNumber object of the index number which the student wants to drop.
        Throws:
        CourseInWaitListException
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException
        CourseRegisteredException
        NoVacancyException
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException
        MaxAuExceededException
